Selena Gomez
Selena Gomez’s career took off in 2007 when she played a beloved role on Disney’s Wizards of Waverly Place. Since then, she has built a hugely diverse and prosperous empire in a variety of creative fields.
The star’s early career was dominated by her work as an actress and musician; both her band Selena Gomez and the Scene and her solo work have resulted in smash hits for the Disney machine and beyond. As an executive producer, Selena has worked on numerous successful television projects, most notably The Wizards Return: Selena and the Chef, Alex vs. Alex, 13 Reasons Why, and Only Murders in the Building.
With “My Mind & Me,” Selena Gomez documented her life in the spotlight.
In 2020 she sent off her own special make-up line Uncommon Excellence, the smart undertaking is depicted as “in excess of a stunner brand”, the organization has proceeded to generate a few religious items among fans and then some. As per TooFab, Uncommon Magnificence created an eye-watering $60 million of every 2021, which contributes a gigantic piece towards Selena’s claimed $95 million total assets.
Selena also co-founded the mental health media platform Wonder mind in 2021, and the following year, she released My Mind & Me, a deeply personal album. The documentary followed Gomez for six years as she struggled with her mental and physical health as well as her struggle with fame.
